        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Yes, and this is also the case in the current PR diff. Unfortunately I think the only way to avoid this would be to know in `on_line` that this is the last `on_line` call, which we can't know with this current design.\r\n\r\n(If we know this, then we can specifically only apply the multiline mark when `on_line` is on the mark's last line, or when it is the last `on_line` call, in the case that the multiline mark continues off screen)",
